parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
even with the foot on the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil springs can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the tire ruptures or the vehicle becomes unstable.
symptoms: Broken or fractured coil springs
uneven tire wear
vibration while driving
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension system can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the vehicle becomes unstable or difficult to steer.
symptoms: Vibration while driving
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering
and clunking or knocking noises from the suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and revving can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the vehicle suddenly accelerates or decelerates.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or revving
difficulty shifting gears
and unusual noises from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator system can cause engine overheating, damage, or failure, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brown or contaminated antifreeze
overheating engine
and radiator leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window and windshield wiper systems can cause visibility problems, accidents, or injuries, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: Windows that do not roll up or down
and faulty windshield wipers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Throttle Body/Cruise Control Cable Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body or cruise control cable can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels soft
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed
the engine RPMs increase rapidly
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle accelerates when brake pedal is depressed
vehicle fails to stop
brake warning indicator illuminates.
